### R1 + R2 discipline (default cortex acceptance criteria)

These are added automatically — keep them unless you have a strong reason to suppress.

- **R1.web-research** (`file_predicate`): if the task depends on external library/framework state, a research memo exists at `$CORTEX_DATA_HOME/research/<topic>-<date>.md` with ≥3 cited URLs before any implementation commit.
- **R2.review-pipeline** (`shell`): for any non-trivial diff (>20 LoC or touches Rule 1 surfaces), `~/.claude/shared/prompts/code-review.md` review pipeline runs and surfaces zero HIGH findings before commit.
- **R3.tests-green** (`shell`): `npm test` exits 0 (or project equivalent — `pytest`, `cargo test`, ...) before any commit.
- **R4.no-secrets** (`regex`): no commit body or staged file matches `(AKIA|sk-[a-zA-Z0-9]{20,}|password\s*=\s*['"]\w)`.

